review_blob: 750ml. the beer appeers to smell extreamly sweet, pour with much carbonation, hazy , thick texture, sticky lips, alotta apple heavy cloying sweetness, full body,
Sample taster at wurstkuche, Honestly it tasted like a Summer seasonal Newcastle and i hate that taste. i wouldnt buy it again, in my case i wouldnt taste it again
sample taster, the alcohol hides very well , had alot of fruity notes to it, pours out light brown color with lively head with some bready notes as well
ON tap at Wurstkuche in LA, Very dark pour ith dark brown head with fruity accented notes and chocolate, definitly not a good beer with really spicy foods like sausage, amazing beer overall!
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: 12 oz bottle. amazing smell of hops! floral, amber, clear, frothy, medium sweetness, medium bitterness, full body, sticky, lively, bitter,

on tap. Pours an orange yellow haze with a thick foam head. Has an aroma of farmhouse funk. Tastes of a sweet saison with malts and hops balance of a belgian strong ale. This is clearly a balance between a light sweet saison and a matly belgian strong. Very good brew.

on tap at bruery. Pours a hazy gold, with a brillant white rocky head that sticks around leaving some nice lacing. Aroma is of citrus, yeast, honey, earthyness and floral tones. Taste is very earthy and spicey, the brett gives this beer a tangy kick. Finish is dry with medium mouthfeel.

on tap at bruery. Murky brown color with a towering head that settles down to only large. Strong aroma of rye, maybe some caraway, nuts, dark chocolate. Strong, rich, dark malt flavor. Lots of breadiness. Chocolate, a bit of dark fruit. Some rye spiciness. Full body.

750ml.  Very dark brown pour with a tan head. Aroma is more porter like and heavier than would be expected. Mostly chocolate and sweet malts. Flavor is very smoky malts with chocolate and coffee. Finishes very dry with a nice alcohol warmth for the season.

750ml bpttle. Pours a deep red, thin head. Aroma is incredible. Spicy pumpkin, clove, cinnamon, sweet malts, slight roast, brown sugar, nutmeg. Mild spicy taste. the yams really come through. Sweet candy sugar? Hides the ABV very well. A great winter sipper if you ask me and one of the top pumpkin beers around.

On tap at the bruery. Color was a bright gold semi clear with a white head. Aromas of slight sweet malt and somw citrus. Nice and smooth in your mouth with some carbonation. Medium light body. Solid bitter hops with a good malt balance. Finish is on the drier side. Good beer.

On tap at the brewery. A light golden color, cloudy. Aroma is full of spice, coriander definitely in there. After it warmed up the malt balanced nicely with the fruitiness of the yeast and the spices. Clean, refreshing, and easy drinking. Great beer.

12oz. glass at sone brewery,This isnt for everyone. Its got some serious bite to it, but the oaking gives is a nice, full flavor. I highly recommend it with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Makes a great float.
16oz glass at Stone brewery,Color is an almost black dark brown with a tan head.The aroma is a rosted coffee and chocolate.Flavor is dark chocolate, rosted coffee, a little smokyness with a hop bite.

16oz glass at Stone brewery on tap,This Porter is a deep reddish brown with a small, creamy off-white head that sticks around. The aroma is a strong dark malt with molasses, coffee, toffee, vanilla, licorice-- its complex! The flavor seets lightly sweet and lightly bitter. The body is creamy and chewy. It has a little alcohol in the aftertaste. Love it.

16oz glass on tap at Stone brewery,This is a good hefe. Pours a hazy orange with white head. Bread, sweet malt, banana, a bit of sourness, clove, spice, and nutty wheat. Nice easy drinking beer. Well done.

8oz. taster from brewery,Creamy medium brown head, black, black, black colour. Aroma of roasted coffee and malts, alcohol, fruits, licorice and some chocolate. Flavour is full of coffee, roasted malts, sugar, alcohol, rich yet almost too balanced. Thick oily mouthfeel, little to no carbonation.  Very well made brew, well balanced and complex only drawback from my perspective is that it is almost too balanced, with an imp like this one expects more of a punch in the face.

8 oz taster at brewery, Medium brown color with a light malty aroma. Body is smooth, sweet and nutty. Very lighty and appropriately hopped, especially coming from the west coast. Finish is roasted and long lasting. This is one of the best brown ales Ive had.
beer_name: AleSmith Nut Brown English-Style Ale (Bottle and Draft)

review_blob: 12 oz bottle, very light golden color im guessing by that its a perfect summer beer, as i drink  it i notice its really dry on the palate, cereal, thin feel, light body, soft carbonation, astringent,

550ml bottle, very dark pour, very flavorful roast coffee and chocolate after taste, dry feel towards the end with an abrupt scent through the nose,red, brown, tan foam, minimal head, medium sweetness, lightly bitter, medium body, slick feel, average carbonation, average carbonation,

12 oz glass on tap, Appearance: Pours a clear, new penny copper-colored body with a small white head. Smell: Sweetish toffee malts with a hefty dose of therapeutic citrus oils (maybe a hint of pine, too). Taste: No more of those sweetish malts as we jump right into the resinous, citrusy hops with a moderate bitterness. Back of the throat acidity. Long, lingering aftertaste. Mouthfeel: Medium-thin body. Medium carbonation. Conspicuously oily. Drinkability: Nice enough for an indiscreet, unbalanced IPA.
From 750ml,Maple syrup,brown sugar , just one of the best of the best for a fall seasonal beer.Great beer buy all you can, lots and lots of  yams mmmMMM thanksgiving in a bottle staight up!
beer_name: The Bruery Autumn Maple Barrel Aged
